The paper discusses techniques for analyzing internet worms and network traffic, which are relevant to the fields of computer security (cs.CR) and networking (cs.NI). The use of Kolmogorov Complexity and compression algorithms also suggests a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also mentions the development of new plugins for Snort, a popular intrusion detection system, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
